{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1200,"text":"When I was a child,\nI knew I had superpowers."},{"time":6920,"text":"That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9280,"text":"I thought I was absolutely amazing\nbecause I could understand"},{"time":13320,"text":"and relate to the feelings\nof brown people,"},{"time":15480,"text":"like my grandfather,\na conservative Muslim guy."},{"time":19360,"text":"And also, I could understand\nmy Afghan mother, my Pakistani father,"},{"time":24280,"text":"not so religious\nbut laid-back, fairly liberal."},{"time":28480,"text":"And of course, I could understand"},{"time":30120,"text":"and relate to the feelings\nof white people."},{"time":32560,"text":"The white Norwegians of my country."},{"time":35480,"text":"You know, white, brown, whatever --"},{"time":38080,"text":"I loved them all."},{"time":39920,"text":"I understood them all,"},{"time":41200,"text":"even if they didn't always\nunderstand each other;"},{"time":43560,"text":"they were all my people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45600,"text":"My father, though,\nwas always really worried."},{"time":48560,"text":"He kept saying that\neven with the best education,"},{"time":51920,"text":"I was not going to get a fair shake."},{"time":55120,"text":"I would still face discrimination,\naccording to him."},{"time":58560,"text":"And that the only way\nto be accepted by white people"},{"time":61400,"text":"would be to become famous."},{"time":63600,"text":"Now, mind you, he had this conversation\nwith me when I was seven years old."},{"time":68440,"text":"So while I'm seven years old, he said,"},{"time":71440,"text":"\"Look, so it's either got to be sports,\nor it's got to be music.\""},{"time":74840,"text":"He didn't know anything about sports --\nbless him -- so it was music."},{"time":79320,"text":"So when I was seven years old,\nhe gathered all my toys, all my dolls,"},{"time":83680,"text":"and he threw them all away."},{"time":86160,"text":"In exchange he gave me\na crappy little Casio keyboard and --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91280,"text":"Yeah. And singing lessons."},{"time":93320,"text":"And he forced me, basically, to practice\nfor hours and hours every single day."},{"time":98120,"text":"Very quickly, he also had me performing\nfor larger and larger audiences,"},{"time":102400,"text":"and bizarrely, I became\nalmost a kind of poster child"},{"time":106200,"text":"for Norwegian multiculturalism."},{"time":108760,"text":"I felt very proud, of course."},{"time":110520,"text":"Because even the newspapers at this point"},{"time":113880,"text":"were starting to write\nnice things about brown people,"},{"time":116480,"text":"so I could feel\nthat my superpower was growing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120960,"text":"So when I was 12 years old,\nwalking home from school,"},{"time":123960,"text":"I took a little detour"},{"time":125200,"text":"because I wanted to buy\nmy favorite sweets called \"salty feet.\""},{"time":128759,"text":"I know they sound kind of awful,"},{"time":131640,"text":"but I absolutely love them."},{"time":133160,"text":"They're basically these little\nsalty licorice bits in the shape of feet."},{"time":138120,"text":"And now that I say it out loud,\nI realize how terrible that sounds,"},{"time":144280,"text":"but be that as it may,\nI absolutely love them."},{"time":146800,"text":"So on my way into the store,"},{"time":148920,"text":"there was this grown white guy\nin the doorway blocking my way."},{"time":153480,"text":"So I tried to walk around him,\nand as I did that, he stopped me"},{"time":159440,"text":"and he was staring at me,"},{"time":162200,"text":"and he spit in my face, and he said,"},{"time":164160,"text":"\"Get out of my way"},{"time":165400,"text":"you little black bitch,\nyou little Paki bitch,"},{"time":168680,"text":"go back home where you came from.\""},{"time":171600,"text":"I was absolutely horrified."},{"time":174720,"text":"I was staring at him."},{"time":176040,"text":"I was too afraid\nto wipe the spit off my face,"},{"time":179840,"text":"even as it was mixing with my tears."},{"time":182000,"text":"I remember looking around,\nhoping that any minute now,"},{"time":185720,"text":"a grown-up is going to come\nand make this guy stop."},{"time":189400,"text":"But instead, people kept hurrying past me\nand pretended not to see me."},{"time":194160,"text":"I was very confused\nbecause I was thinking, well,"},{"time":198640,"text":"\"My white people, come on!\nWhere are they? What's going on?"},{"time":201960,"text":"How come they're not\ncoming and rescuing me?\""},{"time":204760,"text":"So, needless to say,\nI didn't buy the sweets."},{"time":207040,"text":"I just ran home as fast as I could."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210040,"text":"Things were still OK, though, I thought."},{"time":212800,"text":"As time went on,\nthe more successful I became,"},{"time":215920,"text":"I eventually started also\nattracting harassment from brown people."},{"time":221520,"text":"Some men in my parent's community\nfelt that it was unacceptable"},{"time":224840,"text":"and dishonorable for a woman\nto be involved in music"},{"time":229720,"text":"and to be so present in the media."},{"time":233280,"text":"So very quickly, I was starting\nto become attacked at my own concerts."},{"time":238720,"text":"I remember one of the concerts,\nI was onstage, I lean into the audience"},{"time":243760,"text":"and the last thing I see\nis a young brown face,"},{"time":247040,"text":"and the next thing I know is some sort\nof chemical is thrown in my eyes"},{"time":251280,"text":"and I remember I couldn't really see\nand my eyes were watering"},{"time":254520,"text":"but I kept singing anyway."},{"time":256839,"text":"I was spit in the face in the streets\nof Oslo, this time by brown men."},{"time":262360,"text":"They even tried to kidnap me at one point."},{"time":265600,"text":"The death threats were endless."},{"time":267680,"text":"I remember one older bearded guy\nstopped me in the street one time,"},{"time":270960,"text":"and he said, \"The reason\nI hate you so much"},{"time":273120,"text":"is because you make our daughters think"},{"time":275200,"text":"they can do whatever they want.\""},{"time":278560,"text":"A younger guy warned me to watch my back."},{"time":281400,"text":"He said music is un-Islamic\nand the job of whores,"},{"time":284440,"text":"and if you keep this up,\nyou are going to be raped"},{"time":287200,"text":"and your stomach will be cut out so that\nanother whore like you will not be born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293560,"text":"Again, I was so confused."},{"time":295280,"text":"I couldn't understand what was going on."},{"time":297209,"text":"My brown people now starting\nto treat me like this -- how come?"},{"time":301560,"text":"Instead of bridging the worlds,\nthe two worlds,"},{"time":304680,"text":"I felt like I was falling\nbetween my two worlds."},{"time":308000,"text":"I suppose, for me, spit was kryptonite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312560,"text":"So by the time I was 17 years old,"},{"time":314600,"text":"the death threats were endless,\nand the harassment was constant."},{"time":317640,"text":"It got so bad, at one point\nmy mother sat me down and said,"},{"time":320426,"text":"\"Look, we can no longer protect you,\nwe can no longer keep you safe,"},{"time":323920,"text":"so you're going to have to go.\""},{"time":325720,"text":"So I bought a one-way ticket to London,\nI packed my suitcase and I left."},{"time":332160,"text":"My biggest heartbreak at that point\nwas that nobody said anything."},{"time":335880,"text":"I had a very public exit from Norway."},{"time":339120,"text":"My brown people, my white people --\nnobody said anything."},{"time":342680,"text":"Nobody said, \"Hold on, this is wrong."},{"time":345960,"text":"Support this girl, protect this girl,\nbecause she is one of us.\""},{"time":349680,"text":"Nobody said that."},{"time":351320,"text":"Instead, I felt like --\nyou know at the airport,"},{"time":355120,"text":"on the baggage carousel\nyou have these different suitcases"},{"time":358000,"text":"going around and around,"},{"time":359280,"text":"and there's always\nthat one suitcase left at the end,"},{"time":361800,"text":"the one that nobody wants,\nthe one that nobody comes to claim."},{"time":364840,"text":"I felt like that."},{"time":367040,"text":"I'd never felt so alone.\nI'd never felt so lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372360,"text":"So, after coming to London,\nI did eventually resume my music career."},{"time":377000,"text":"Different place, but unfortunately\nthe same old story."},{"time":380840,"text":"I remember a message sent to me\nsaying that I was going to be killed"},{"time":384400,"text":"and that rivers of blood\nwere going to flow"},{"time":387800,"text":"and that I was going to be raped\nmany times before I died."},{"time":391280,"text":"By this point, I have to say,"},{"time":392720,"text":"I was actually getting used\nto messages like this,"},{"time":395200,"text":"but what became different was that\nnow they started threatening my family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400760,"text":"So once again, I packed my suitcase,\nI left music and I moved to the US."},{"time":406520,"text":"I'd had enough."},{"time":407800,"text":"I didn't want to have anything\nto do with this anymore."},{"time":410440,"text":"And I was certainly not\ngoing to be killed for something"},{"time":413120,"text":"that wasn't even my dream --\nit was my father's choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418200,"text":"So I kind of got lost."},{"time":421400,"text":"I kind of fell apart."},{"time":422960,"text":"But I decided that what I wanted to do"},{"time":425320,"text":"is spend the next\nhowever many years of my life"},{"time":428680,"text":"supporting young people"},{"time":430360,"text":"and to try to be there in some small way,"},{"time":433280,"text":"whatever way that I could."},{"time":435000,"text":"I started volunteering\nfor various organizations"},{"time":438280,"text":"that were working\nwith young Muslims inside of Europe."},{"time":444080,"text":"And, to my surprise, what I found was"},{"time":447120,"text":"so many of these young people\nwere suffering and struggling."},{"time":452440,"text":"They were facing so many problems\nwith their families and their communities"},{"time":456000,"text":"who seemed to care more\nabout their honor and their reputation"},{"time":459640,"text":"than the happiness\nand the lives of their own kids."},{"time":463760,"text":"I started feeling like maybe I wasn't\nso alone, maybe I wasn't so weird."},{"time":468280,"text":"Maybe there are more\nof my people out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471280,"text":"The thing is, what most people\ndon't understand"},{"time":473520,"text":"is that there are so many of us\ngrowing up in Europe"},{"time":477840,"text":"who are not free to be ourselves."},{"time":480280,"text":"We're not allowed to be who we are."},{"time":483360,"text":"We are not free to marry"},{"time":487440,"text":"or to be in relationships\nwith people that we choose."},{"time":490400,"text":"We can't even pick our own career."},{"time":492080,"text":"This is the norm in the Muslim\nheartlands of Europe."},{"time":495880,"text":"Even in the freest societies\nin the world, we're not free."},{"time":499640,"text":"Our lives, our dreams, our future\ndoes not belong to us,"},{"time":503560,"text":"it belongs to our parents\nand their community."},{"time":506840,"text":"I found endless stories of young people"},{"time":510880,"text":"who are lost to all of us,"},{"time":513799,"text":"who are invisible to all of us"},{"time":515559,"text":"but who are suffering,\nand they are suffering alone."},{"time":519520,"text":"Kids we are losing to forced marriages,\nto honor-based violence and abuse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525280,"text":"Eventually, I realized after several\nyears of working with these young people,"},{"time":529000,"text":"that I will not be able to keep running."},{"time":531040,"text":"I can't spend the rest of my life\nbeing scared and hiding"},{"time":535720,"text":"and that I'm actually\ngoing to have to do something."},{"time":539640,"text":"And I also realized\nthat my silence, our silence,"},{"time":542760,"text":"allows abuse like this to continue."},{"time":546000,"text":"So I decided that I wanted to put\nmy childhood superpower to some use"},{"time":550520,"text":"by trying to make people on the different\nsides of these issues understand"},{"time":555240,"text":"what it's like to be a young person stuck\nbetween your family and your country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560960,"text":"So I started making films,\nand I started telling these stories."},{"time":564880,"text":"And I also wanted people to understand\nthe deadly consequences of us"},{"time":569320,"text":"not taking these problems seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"So the first film I made was about Banaz."},{"time":575440,"text":"She was a 17-year-old\nKurdish girl in London."},{"time":579520,"text":"She was obedient, she did\nwhatever her parents wanted."},{"time":582840,"text":"She tried to do everything right."},{"time":585280,"text":"She married some guy\nthat her parents chose for her,"},{"time":587920,"text":"even though he beat\nand raped her constantly."},{"time":591880,"text":"And when she tried to go\nto her family for help, they said,"},{"time":594720,"text":"\"Well, you got to go back\nand be a better wife.\""},{"time":597000,"text":"Because they didn't want\na divorced daughter on their hands"},{"time":599840,"text":"because, of course, that would\nbring dishonor on the family."},{"time":603680,"text":"She was beaten so badly\nher ears would bleed,"},{"time":607200,"text":"and when she finally left\nand she found a young man that she chose"},{"time":612320,"text":"and she fell in love with,"},{"time":614160,"text":"the community and the family found out"},{"time":616440,"text":"and she disappeared."},{"time":618440,"text":"She was found three months later."},{"time":621200,"text":"She'd been stuffed into a suitcase\nand buried underneath the house."},{"time":628040,"text":"She had been strangled,\nshe had been beaten to death"},{"time":632760,"text":"by three men, three cousins,\non the orders of her father and uncle."},{"time":637960,"text":"The added tragedy of Banaz's story"},{"time":640160,"text":"is that she had gone to the police\nin England five times asking for help,"},{"time":646080,"text":"telling them that she was\ngoing to be killed by her family."},{"time":649160,"text":"The police didn't believe her\nso they didn't do anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653080,"text":"And the problem with this"},{"time":654360,"text":"is that not only are so many of our kids\nfacing these problems"},{"time":658760,"text":"within their families\nand within their families' communities,"},{"time":661880,"text":"but they're also meeting misunderstandings"},{"time":666640,"text":"and apathy in the countries\nthat they grow up in."},{"time":671640,"text":"When their own families betray them,\nthey look to the rest of us,"},{"time":676360,"text":"and when we don't understand,"},{"time":678440,"text":"we lose them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681120,"text":"So while I was making this film,\nseveral people said to me,"},{"time":684320,"text":"\"Well, Deeyah, you know,\nthis is just their culture,"},{"time":686880,"text":"this is just what those people\ndo to their kids"},{"time":689095,"text":"and we can't really interfere.\""},{"time":691880,"text":"I can assure you\nbeing murdered is not my culture."},{"time":696280,"text":"You know?"},{"time":697520,"text":"And surely people who look like me,"},{"time":699240,"text":"young women who come\nfrom backgrounds like me,"},{"time":701760,"text":"should be subject to the same rights,\nthe same protections"},{"time":705880,"text":"as anybody else in our country, why not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":710360,"text":"So, for my next film,\nI wanted to try and understand"},{"time":715120,"text":"why some of our young\nMuslim kids in Europe"},{"time":718000,"text":"are drawn to extremism and violence."},{"time":720880,"text":"But with that topic,"},{"time":722160,"text":"I also recognized that I was going\nto have to face my worst fear:"},{"time":727040,"text":"the brown men with beards."},{"time":730880,"text":"The same men, or similar men,"},{"time":733720,"text":"to the ones that have hounded me\nfor most of my life."},{"time":737560,"text":"Men that I've been afraid of\nmost of my life."},{"time":740280,"text":"Men that I've also deeply disliked,"},{"time":743160,"text":"for many, many years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745160,"text":"So I spent the next two years\ninterviewing convicted terrorists,"},{"time":749160,"text":"jihadis and former extremists."},{"time":751680,"text":"What I already knew,\nwhat was very obvious already,"},{"time":755040,"text":"was that religion, politics,\nEurope's colonial baggage,"},{"time":760240,"text":"also Western foreign policy\nfailures of recent years,"},{"time":764520,"text":"were all a part of the picture."},{"time":766520,"text":"But what I was more interested\nin finding out was what are the human,"},{"time":769800,"text":"what are the personal reasons"},{"time":771400,"text":"why some of our young people\nare susceptible to groups like this."},{"time":777000,"text":"And what really surprised me\nwas that I found wounded human beings."},{"time":783760,"text":"Instead of the monsters\nthat I was looking for,"},{"time":786240,"text":"that I was hoping to find --"},{"time":787640,"text":"quite frankly because\nit would have been very satisfying --"},{"time":790800,"text":"I found broken people."},{"time":793520,"text":"Just like Banaz,"},{"time":795040,"text":"I found that these young men\nwere torn apart"},{"time":798320,"text":"from trying to bridge the gaps"},{"time":800880,"text":"between their families\nand the countries that they were born in."},{"time":805720,"text":"And what I also learned\nis that extremist groups, terrorist groups"},{"time":809120,"text":"are taking advantage\nof these feelings of our young people"},{"time":812600,"text":"and channeling that -- cynically --\nchanneling that toward violence."},{"time":816480,"text":"\"Come to us,\" they say."},{"time":818080,"text":"\"Reject both sides,\nyour family and your country"},{"time":821080,"text":"because they reject you."},{"time":822760,"text":"For your family, their honor\nis more important than you"},{"time":825880,"text":"and for your country,"},{"time":827160,"text":"a real Norwegian, Brit or a French person\nwill always be white and never you.\""},{"time":834040,"text":"They're also promising our young people\nthe things that they crave:"},{"time":837520,"text":"significance, heroism,\na sense of belonging and purpose,"},{"time":841880,"text":"a community that loves and accepts them."},{"time":845200,"text":"They make the powerless feel powerful."},{"time":848160,"text":"The invisible and the silent\nare finally seen and heard."},{"time":855120,"text":"This is what they're doing\nfor our young people."},{"time":857680,"text":"Why are these groups doing this\nfor our young people and not us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":862760,"text":"The thing is,"},{"time":864360,"text":"I'm not trying to justify"},{"time":867720,"text":"or excuse any of the violence."},{"time":871480,"text":"What I am trying to say\nis that we have to understand"},{"time":875080,"text":"why some of our young people\nare attracted to this."},{"time":879680,"text":"I would like to also show you, actually --"},{"time":882040,"text":"these are childhood photos\nof some of the guys in the film."},{"time":887240,"text":"What really struck me\nis that so many of them --"},{"time":890960,"text":"I never would have thought this --"},{"time":892640,"text":"but so many of them\nhave absent or abusive fathers."},{"time":896800,"text":"And several of these young guys"},{"time":898760,"text":"ended up finding caring\nand compassionate father figures"},{"time":902920,"text":"within these extremist groups."},{"time":905920,"text":"I also found men\nbrutalized by racist violence,"},{"time":909800,"text":"but who found a way\nto stop feeling like victims"},{"time":912080,"text":"by becoming violent themselves."},{"time":913600,"text":"In fact, I found something,\nto my horror, that I recognized."},{"time":918920,"text":"I found the same feelings that I felt\nas a 17-year-old as I fled from Norway."},{"time":926160,"text":"The same confusion, the same sorrow,"},{"time":929560,"text":"the same feeling of being betrayed"},{"time":934760,"text":"and not belonging to anyone."},{"time":938560,"text":"The same feeling of being lost\nand torn between cultures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942760,"text":"Having said that,\nI did not choose destruction,"},{"time":945320,"text":"I chose to pick up a camera\ninstead of a gun."},{"time":948080,"text":"And the reason I did that\nis because of my superpower."},{"time":951440,"text":"I could see that understanding\nis the answer, instead of violence."},{"time":956360,"text":"Seeing human beings"},{"time":958080,"text":"with all their virtues and all their flaws"},{"time":961840,"text":"instead of continuing the caricatures:"},{"time":963720,"text":"the us and them, the villains and victims."},{"time":966400,"text":"I'd also finally\ncome to terms with the fact"},{"time":968520,"text":"that my two cultures\ndidn't have to be on a collision course"},{"time":972200,"text":"but instead became a space\nwhere I found my own voice."},{"time":975840,"text":"I stopped feeling\nlike I had to pick a side,"},{"time":978600,"text":"but this took me many, many years."},{"time":981640,"text":"There are so many\nof our young people today"},{"time":983680,"text":"who are struggling with these same issues,"},{"time":985720,"text":"and they're struggling with this alone."},{"time":989440,"text":"And this leaves them open like wounds."},{"time":992560,"text":"And for some, the worldview\nof radical Islam"},{"time":995640,"text":"becomes the infection\nthat festers in these open wounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001160,"text":"There's an African proverb that says,"},{"time":1005960,"text":"\"If the young are not\ninitiated into the village,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"they will burn it down\njust to feel its warmth.\""},{"time":1013240,"text":"I would like to ask --"},{"time":1015640,"text":"to Muslim parents and Muslim communities,"},{"time":1018200,"text":"will you love and care for your children"},{"time":1020640,"text":"without forcing them\nto meet your expectations?"},{"time":1023440,"text":"Can you choose them instead of your honor?"},{"time":1026400,"text":"Can you understand\nwhy they're so angry and alienated"},{"time":1029440,"text":"when you put your honor\nbefore their happiness?"},{"time":1032520,"text":"Can you try to be a friend to your child"},{"time":1035119,"text":"so that they can trust you"},{"time":1036920,"text":"and want to share with you\ntheir experiences,"},{"time":1039240,"text":"rather than having\nto seek it somewhere else?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042359,"text":"And to our young people\ntempted by extremism,"},{"time":1046680,"text":"can you acknowledge\nthat your rage is fueled by pain?"},{"time":1051640,"text":"Will you find the strength\nto resist those cynical old men"},{"time":1055080,"text":"who want to use your blood\nfor their own profits?"},{"time":1059040,"text":"Can you find a way to live?"},{"time":1061880,"text":"Can you see that the sweetest revenge"},{"time":1064160,"text":"is for you to live\na happy, full and free life?"},{"time":1067640,"text":"A life defined by you and nobody else."},{"time":1070560,"text":"Why do you want to become\njust another dead Muslim kid?"},{"time":1075080,"text":"And for the rest of us, when will we start\nlistening to our young people?"},{"time":1080520,"text":"How can we support them"},{"time":1081800,"text":"in redirecting their pain\ninto something more constructive?"},{"time":1086760,"text":"They think we don't like them."},{"time":1088240,"text":"They think we don't care\nwhat happens to them."},{"time":1091040,"text":"They think we don't accept them."},{"time":1092840,"text":"Can we find a way\nto make them feel differently?"},{"time":1097280,"text":"What will it take for us\nto see them and notice them"},{"time":1100240,"text":"before they become either the victims\nor the perpetrators of violence?"},{"time":1105200,"text":"Can we make ourselves care about them\nand consider them to be our own?"},{"time":1108800,"text":"And not just be outraged when the victims\nof violence look like ourselves?"},{"time":1113680,"text":"Can we find a way to reject hatred\nand heal the divisions between us?"},{"time":1118720,"text":"The thing is we cannot afford\nto give up on each other or on our kids,"},{"time":1122720,"text":"even if they've given up on us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124880,"text":"We are all in this together."},{"time":1127080,"text":"And in the long term, revenge and violence\nwill not work against extremists."},{"time":1133480,"text":"Terrorists want us\nto huddle in our houses in fear,"},{"time":1137280,"text":"closing our doors and our hearts."},{"time":1139480,"text":"They want us to tear open\nmore wounds in our societies"},{"time":1143320,"text":"so that they can use them\nto spread their infection more widely."},{"time":1146880,"text":"They want us to become like them:"},{"time":1149600,"text":"intolerant, hateful and cruel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154200,"text":"The day after the Paris attacks,"},{"time":1156680,"text":"a friend of mine\nsent this photo of her daughter."},{"time":1160800,"text":"This is a white girl and an Arab girl."},{"time":1163280,"text":"They're best friends."},{"time":1165120,"text":"This image is the kryptonite\nfor extremists."},{"time":1171240,"text":"These two little girls\nwith their superpowers"},{"time":1174320,"text":"are showing the way forward"},{"time":1175840,"text":"towards a society\nthat we need to build together,"},{"time":1180120,"text":"a society that includes and supports,"},{"time":1184480,"text":"rather than rejects our kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1187960,"text":"Thank you for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1189320,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}